    {
      "id": "BYtC",
      "code_hash": "44698f00552c012bf008d3b4156fe264",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"key-insights\">Key Insights</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Indonesia achieved the most dramatic transformation: from 6.7% to 90.6% clean fuel access in 23 years</li>\n<li>India's Ujjwala Yojana program drove access from 22.7% to 76.7%, lifting hundreds of millions out of solid fuel dependence</li>\n<li>China went from 40.3% to 88.7%, driven by urbanization and natural gas infrastructure</li>\n<li>Ethiopia remains at just 7.1% -- nearly the entire population still cooks with wood, charcoal, or dung</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
